data.title: Can you keep a secret?
data.text: This out of the way restaurant is as good as any in Lake Elsinore. One of the secrets is the sample taco plate. Beef, Chicken and pork with lime, lemon, chilies and some Spanish onions for good measure. Just $6.00 + tax out the door. Being a seller at the Art on Main street, this is a sweet deal while selling Art.

data.title: Watch out!
data.text: my husband took me to this place off the beaten path to get some delicious authentic Mexican food. That was for sure I got a Carnitas and carne Taco plate and my husband got a taquito plate. There was a lovely landscaped outdoor eating area with a fountain. I noticed a few B's hiring around it and I'm not allergic so I didn't think anything of it. But as soon as our food came out they started swarming. Not bees, Hornets. They're attracted by the smell of the meat and no matter how many times I tried to swat them away with my hand or napkin or eventually my shoe, they kept coming. We even got up and moved to a table that was farther away from the fountain and they kept following us. It made the dining experience overall unpleasant. We didn't even finish really. Had to run to the car to be left alone since there was no indoor dining area

data.title: Lunch with a friend.
data.text: We were on the freeway trying to decide where to eat. I remembered this place from a previous visit and we had lunch there. It was great. Friendly service, a nice location and lots of smiles.

data.title: Teax Mix in Elsinore///
data.text: We went for a family meeting...lots of good food to choose from...Great time....Good Drinks and it was in down Town.

data.title: Best Mexican Food In Lake Elsinore
data.text: Coming from the Los Angeles area, and an abundance of amazing Mexican restaurants. Plus grandmas house is always open. I found myself missing the homemade Mexican food I could get on any corner. I've eaten at every Mexican restaurant in Lake Elsinore BLAH canned food. Till I found this little whole in the wall, on a corner...in a park. Makes my mouth water just thinking about it, and reminds me of what i'm missing at grandmas. Try the chili verde and eggs.....
